  <description><![CDATA[<p>As back to nature <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/lakes-mountains-holidays/resorts/canada" title="canada">Canadian</a> holidays go, you’ll find it hard to beat the great outdoors of Alberta for fresh air, lovely lakes and majestic snow-capped mountains.<br />The forested Rocky Mountains create a rain shadow over this sunny Canadian province which is home to five UNESCO world heritage sites. A wildlife wonderland with bald eagles, osprey, bears, elk, moose and big horn sheep, <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/lakes-mountains-holidays/resorts/canada/alberta">Alberta</a> is a wonderful wilderness waiting to be discovered, with walking trails, hiking, camping trips and river adventures ready to welcome you to its breathtaking tranquillity.</p>
<p>We feature three resorts here, with the nearby <a href="/{localLink:dfa97055-585a-4080-80bd-3c829c91955e}" title="Banff">Banff</a>, <a href="/{localLink:52d0b490-0d35-4adf-9507-90aa71ec8931}" title="Lake Louise">Lake Louise</a> and <a href="/{localLink:1616b395-87e8-4747-82e9-046ad78b629b}" title="Jasper">Jasper</a> National Parks connected by the beautiful Icefields Parkway. What a great place to unwind.</p>
<p><strong>Banff;</strong> A bustling resort with a good selection of shops, bars and restaurants, Banff is overlooked by the striking Cascade Mountain, and Canada's first ever national park is on the doorstep, so it’s no wonder that it’s such a popular place for holidays in Canada.</p>
<p><strong>Lake Louise;</strong> 58 km north of Banff, Lake Louise is named after Queen Victoria’s fourth daughter (the nearby glacier took her mother’s name). A peaceful place with a handful of shops, it’s a relaxing resort from which to explore.</p>
<p><strong>Jasper;</strong> Further north still, this charming and welcoming frontier town is a brilliant base camp for wildlife expeditions. The scenery will dazzle you with massive glaciers, snow-capped peaks, turquoise lakes and lush flower-filled alpine meadows</p>]]></description>
